WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.251 --> 00:00:02.877
You said the council
had already assembled?

2
00:00:02.961 --> 00:00:04.212
- It has.
- Why don't I hear them?

3
00:00:04.296 --> 00:00:06.297
[gasps]
Is it all of them?

4
00:00:06.381 --> 00:00:08.649
I think so. Witchfinders.

5
00:00:08.882 --> 00:00:10.218
[Tormada] Welcome. Councillor.

6
00:00:10.302 --> 00:00:12.137
Can we still take Pennsa?

7
00:00:12.221 --> 00:00:16.641
Ah. you still underestimate
the power of my bombs.

8
00:00:16.725 --> 00:00:18.601
[Harlan] We just need
to get to Pennsa before Tormada.

9
00:00:18.685 --> 00:00:19.561
You know a faster way?

10
00:00:19.645 --> 00:00:21.646
[Harlan] <i>There's another route.
but it's dangerous.</i>

11
00:00:21.730 --> 00:00:23.273
- [grunting]
- Oh! Fuck! Shit!

12
00:00:23.357 --> 00:00:24.816
- Haniwa.
- [Haniwa screams]

13
00:00:24.900 --> 00:00:27.944
- [grunting]
- [screaming. grunting]

14
00:00:28.028 --> 00:00:31.989
My sister was right.
Violence must be met with violence.

15
00:00:32.073 --> 00:00:34.993
Kofun. I need you to ride back to Pennsa.
tell your mother Tormada's coming.

16
00:00:35.077 --> 00:00:35.994
[Sibeth] <i>Why is he in chains?</i>

17
00:00:36.078 --> 00:00:38.121
That is no way to treat
a new friend and ally.

18
00:00:38.205 --> 00:00:39.831
[both grunting]

19
00:00:39.915 --> 00:00:41.332
[Harlan] It's okay.

20
00:00:41.416 --> 00:00:42.633
[breathes shakily]

21
00:00:42.717 --> 00:00:43.934
Give this to Maghra.

22
00:00:44.311 --> 00:00:46.880
[Tormada] <i>I find myself
wondering how this ends.</i>

23
00:00:46.964 --> 00:00:47.964
- [horse whinnies]
- [grunts]

24
00:00:48.048 --> 00:00:50.592
[Sibeth] <i>If you're careful.
you just might keep your head.</i>

25
00:00:50.676 --> 00:00:54.053
I wore the crown.
but it always felt a little light.

26
00:00:54.152 --> 00:00:58.255
Now that crown will be forged
in the burning flames of war.

27
00:01:06.179 --> 00:01:07.779
[Maddox] Load up! Now!

28
00:01:08.181 --> 00:01:10.240
[soldiers grunting]

29
00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:18.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

30
00:01:32.163 --> 00:01:35.390
Your Majesty. we found this man
riding through the woods.

31
00:01:37.168 --> 00:01:39.144
[necklace rattling]

32
00:01:40.296 --> 00:01:41.521
Sibeth?

33
00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:45.525
Kofun?

34
00:01:47.345 --> 00:01:48.904
Is that really you?

35
00:01:49.723 --> 00:01:52.600
What are you...
What are you doing here? What is this?

36
00:01:52.684 --> 00:01:54.268
[Witchfinder] Kneel for your queen. witch.

37
00:01:54.352 --> 00:01:55.811
- She's not my queen.
- [Sibeth gasps]

38
00:01:55.895 --> 00:01:57.537
[grunting]

39
00:01:59.107 --> 00:02:02.918
Poor Kofun.
Always and forever a step behind.

40
00:02:03.445 --> 00:02:08.257
Though in fairness. I must thank you
for freeing me from my sister's clutches.

41
00:02:08.908 --> 00:02:10.926
You're working with Trivantes.

42
00:02:12.162 --> 00:02:14.669
You're insane.
They're gonna destroy Pennsa.

43
00:02:15.055 --> 00:02:18.716
No. I'm going to destroy Pennsa.

44
00:02:19.294 --> 00:02:20.294
[shouts]

45
00:02:20.378 --> 00:02:23.464
[panting. grunting]

46
00:02:23.548 --> 00:02:25.049
[coughing]

47
00:02:25.133 --> 00:02:26.592
Kofun. don't make me wonder

48
00:02:26.676 --> 00:02:30.572
whether my fondness for you
might be a character flaw.

49
00:02:31.541 --> 00:02:34.015
You're gonna kill thousands.

50
00:02:34.353 --> 00:02:37.116
Maghra should've thought of that
before her little coup.

51
00:02:39.522 --> 00:02:41.663
Tormada. are we ready?

52
00:02:42.108 --> 00:02:43.665
[Tormada] We are. my queen.

53
00:02:43.860 --> 00:02:47.251
Sibeth. please don't do this.

54
00:02:47.530 --> 00:02:48.698
Do it.

55
00:02:48.782 --> 00:02:49.782
[grunts]

56
00:02:49.866 --> 00:02:51.297
[Tormada] On my mark!

57
00:02:51.826 --> 00:02:54.384
Hold on. Kofun.
You won't want to miss this.

58
00:02:55.246 --> 00:02:56.552
Move him.

59
00:02:57.332 --> 00:02:58.638
[fingers snapping]

60
00:03:30.949 --> 00:03:34.841
[walking stick bell jingling]

61
00:03:35.161 --> 00:03:38.511
[Maghra] Why are you troubling yourself
with the burial of traitors?

62
00:03:39.165 --> 00:03:42.265
There is no one else
to say the final prayers for them.

63
00:03:57.058 --> 00:03:58.364
I trained them.

64
00:04:02.022 --> 00:04:03.578
I fought with them.

65
00:04:09.779 --> 00:04:13.629
I never imagined this.

66
00:04:16.161 --> 00:04:17.717
They tried to kill us.

67
00:04:20.874 --> 00:04:25.892
They did what they believed was right.

68
00:04:30.216 --> 00:04:36.277
They've lived their entire life
in the service of an ideal.

69
00:04:38.183 --> 00:04:41.616
We were the ones to change the rules.

70
00:04:46.232 --> 00:04:47.538
[kisses]

71
00:05:03.083 --> 00:05:04.389
Let's go.

72
00:05:06.920 --> 00:05:08.587
[Maghra] How go your preparations?

73
00:05:08.671 --> 00:05:12.550
It's somewhat difficult to prepare
for an enemy we don't know

74
00:05:12.634 --> 00:05:14.468
with weapons we don't understand.

75
00:05:14.552 --> 00:05:16.401
But the army is assembled.

76
00:05:17.472 --> 00:05:19.431
Did you believe what Shiloh said

77
00:05:19.515 --> 00:05:22.143
about Sibeth allying herself
with the Trivantians?

78
00:05:22.227 --> 00:05:26.160
Witchfinders don't lie.
And I put nothing past your sister.

79
00:05:26.940 --> 00:05:30.957
What use would the Trivantians have
for Sibeth or the Witchfinders?

80
00:05:31.194 --> 00:05:35.545
If Tormada is indeed leading
a rogue faction of the Trivantian army.

81
00:05:35.865 --> 00:05:38.451
their numbers might not be
as large as we fear.

82
00:05:38.535 --> 00:05:42.121
Which is why they might have welcomed
an alliance with her.

83
00:05:42.205 --> 00:05:45.930
The numbers won't matter if those bombs
can do what Baba said they can.

84
00:05:52.215 --> 00:05:53.730
[metal clanking]

85
00:06:08.148 --> 00:06:09.662
Armed and ready. sir.

86
00:06:11.317 --> 00:06:15.321
As soon as we reach the palace.
I will order battalions out to the gates.

87
00:06:15.405 --> 00:06:17.754
We'll not allow those weapons
to enter the city.

88
00:06:32.547 --> 00:06:33.936
Fire!

89
00:06:36.092 --> 00:06:37.899
Fire!

90
00:06:38.762 --> 00:06:40.068
[grunts]

91
00:06:44.274 --> 00:06:45.663
[grunts]

92
00:06:49.064 --> 00:06:50.662
[grunts]

93
00:06:58.156 --> 00:06:59.462
[Maghra] Shh.

94
00:06:59.824 --> 00:07:01.784
[bombs whirring]

95
00:07:01.868 --> 00:07:03.174
What is it?

96
00:07:04.537 --> 00:07:06.219
[grunts]

97
00:07:10.251 --> 00:07:12.141
[gasping]

98
00:07:12.712 --> 00:07:14.602
- We're too late.
- No.

99
00:07:19.594 --> 00:07:22.610
[gasps] Oh. my.

100
00:07:23.390 --> 00:07:26.767
[villagers wailing. screaming]

101
00:07:26.851 --> 00:07:29.492
- [sharp ringing]
- [Tamacti Jun coughing]

102
00:07:31.981 --> 00:07:33.287
Maghra!

103
00:07:35.026 --> 00:07:36.374
Maghra!

104
00:07:37.570 --> 00:07:39.822
Tamacti. [Grunts]

105
00:07:39.906 --> 00:07:42.422
[Tamacti Jun]
They've breached the walls. Come.

106
00:07:43.076 --> 00:07:45.341
No. they didn't breach the walls.

107
00:07:45.745 --> 00:07:49.512
The bombs came over the walls.
I heard them fly.

108
00:07:50.333 --> 00:07:51.639
Wolffe.

109
00:07:53.628 --> 00:07:55.101
Again!

110
00:07:57.090 --> 00:07:58.396
[grunts]

111
00:08:08.309 --> 00:08:10.199
[bombs whirring]

112
00:08:19.779 --> 00:08:21.336
[screams]

113
00:08:22.949 --> 00:08:25.785
- Haniwa! Haniwa!
- [villagers screaming. clamoring]

114
00:08:25.869 --> 00:08:29.886
- [Haniwa coughs. panting]
- [Baba Voss grunts]

115
00:08:31.750 --> 00:08:33.806
Keep moving! Go!

116
00:08:45.805 --> 00:08:47.153
[grunts]

117
00:08:48.767 --> 00:08:50.073
Maghra!

118
00:08:50.769 --> 00:08:52.603
- Maghra.
- Papa! We can't find her.

119
00:08:52.687 --> 00:08:54.786
- Keep moving. Okay?
- Okay.

120
00:09:06.785 --> 00:09:08.160
- Wolffe!
- [handmaiden] Here!

121
00:09:08.244 --> 00:09:10.677
[Wolffe crying]

122
00:09:12.374 --> 00:09:13.499
[sighs] We have to move.

123
00:09:13.583 --> 00:09:15.598
- We'll be safer here.
- No. Come on.

124
00:09:17.712 --> 00:09:19.018
Fire!

125
00:09:19.381 --> 00:09:21.562
[drum beating]

126
00:09:30.725 --> 00:09:33.324
[bomb whirring]

127
00:09:37.524 --> 00:09:40.706
No! No! No!

128
00:11:24.923 --> 00:11:26.229
[inhales sharply]

129
00:11:28.385 --> 00:11:29.691
[grunts]

130
00:11:32.972 --> 00:11:35.905
Hello? Who's there?

131
00:11:38.144 --> 00:11:40.284
[Baba Voss] Relax. You're safe.

132
00:11:41.272 --> 00:11:42.578
Where am I?

133
00:11:43.149 --> 00:11:44.872
You are on Alkenny land.

134
00:11:45.485 --> 00:11:50.336
Alkenny? One... One of the hidden tribes?

135
00:11:51.700 --> 00:11:54.674
The way you say that
tells me you're not from a tribe.

136
00:11:57.455 --> 00:11:58.761
No.

137
00:11:59.624 --> 00:12:00.930
Where then?

138
00:12:02.585 --> 00:12:04.211
The Northern Mountains.

139
00:12:04.295 --> 00:12:07.562
[inhales deeply] You've come a long way.

140
00:12:10.135 --> 00:12:11.691
How did I get here?

141
00:12:13.179 --> 00:12:14.610
Don't you remember?

142
00:12:17.350 --> 00:12:19.282
There was a... a woman.

143
00:12:21.479 --> 00:12:23.328
Yes. Paris.

144
00:12:24.149 --> 00:12:27.790
She found you wandering in the snow.
She brought you back to this village.

145
00:12:29.029 --> 00:12:31.210
She says you were running from something.

146
00:12:32.407 --> 00:12:36.424
She says maybe you haven't run far enough.

147
00:12:38.371 --> 00:12:40.887
[Pennsa villagers screaming. wailing]

148
00:12:42.083 --> 00:12:44.752
[gasping. whimpering]

149
00:12:44.836 --> 00:12:46.642
Haniwa. what is it?

150
00:12:47.672 --> 00:12:50.716
The palace is destroyed. Papa.

151
00:12:50.800 --> 00:12:52.760
- Shh.
- [No barking]

152
00:12:52.844 --> 00:12:54.262
What do you hear?

153
00:12:54.346 --> 00:12:56.486
No. No!

154
00:12:59.184 --> 00:13:00.490
[Haniwa grunts]

155
00:13:03.104 --> 00:13:04.410
[Baba Voss] No.

156
00:13:07.859 --> 00:13:09.666
- [No whimpers]
- [Baba Voss] Maghra!

157
00:13:11.488 --> 00:13:12.613
[Wolffe crying]

158
00:13:12.697 --> 00:13:14.657
[Haniwa] Come. baby. Papa.

159
00:13:14.741 --> 00:13:16.381
[Baba Voss] Maghra.

160
00:13:16.910 --> 00:13:19.704
[grunts] Ranger. help me!

161
00:13:19.788 --> 00:13:22.957
[Wolffe crying]

162
00:13:23.041 --> 00:13:24.764
[both groaning]

163
00:13:25.835 --> 00:13:27.169
Baba Voss.

164
00:13:27.253 --> 00:13:29.769
Tamacti Jun. Ranger. help him.

165
00:13:33.343 --> 00:13:36.345
[gasps] Shh. Shh.

166
00:13:36.429 --> 00:13:39.265
She's still breathing. Still breathing.
Maghra.

167
00:13:39.349 --> 00:13:42.657
Tormada. tell me you didn't disappoint.

168
00:13:43.395 --> 00:13:46.911
My Ayuras report all direct hits.
my queen.

169
00:13:47.148 --> 00:13:48.705
[gasps. chuckles]

170
00:13:50.985 --> 00:13:55.712
Kofun. What did you see? Huh?

171
00:13:57.617 --> 00:13:59.757
You bombed your own child.

172
00:14:00.286 --> 00:14:03.414
If he is in harm's way.
it's your mother who has placed him there.

173
00:14:03.498 --> 00:14:05.596
just as she's placed you here.

174
00:14:07.293 --> 00:14:08.599
Fuck you.

175
00:14:08.962 --> 00:14:10.810
Secure him inside my tent.

176
00:14:18.138 --> 00:14:20.069
- Load up!
- Wait. wait. wait.

177
00:14:21.307 --> 00:14:24.741
Let's give my sister some time
to appreciate the position she's in.

178
00:14:25.395 --> 00:14:27.452
The deaths she's caused.

179
00:14:27.897 --> 00:14:29.148
[Tormada] Are you sure?

180
00:14:29.232 --> 00:14:31.873
We've mapped the city.
established key coordinates.

181
00:14:32.318 --> 00:14:33.624
Don't worry.

182
00:14:34.029 --> 00:14:37.531
Knowing my sister.
you'll be launching more soon enough.

183
00:14:37.615 --> 00:14:40.673
[necklace rattling]

184
00:14:52.547 --> 00:14:58.024
[Kofun screams. straining]

185
00:15:06.394 --> 00:15:09.369
- I hear you…
- [splutters]

186
00:15:11.358 --> 00:15:13.623
…struggling against your ties.

187
00:15:15.862 --> 00:15:18.211
And I can't help but feel

188
00:15:19.199 --> 00:15:22.340
that that's what you've been doing
since I've known you.

189
00:15:23.370 --> 00:15:26.831
struggling against these invisible ties
that bind you.

190
00:15:26.915 --> 00:15:28.708
[Kofun breathing heavily]

191
00:15:28.792 --> 00:15:32.266
You cannot get free.
but you never stop trying.

192
00:15:33.463 --> 00:15:35.978
I think it's what I love most about you.

193
00:15:36.966 --> 00:15:40.817
You don't love me.
You don't know anything about love.

194
00:15:41.221 --> 00:15:42.513
On the contrary.

195
00:15:42.597 --> 00:15:46.197
If anything. I love too much. too deeply.

196
00:15:47.644 --> 00:15:52.078
That's why I allowed myself to believe
Maghra wouldn't betray me again.

197
00:15:53.983 --> 00:15:55.915
If you love me. you won't kill me.

198
00:15:56.695 --> 00:15:59.002
[laughs]

199
00:16:00.240 --> 00:16:01.240
[grunts]

200
00:16:01.324 --> 00:16:04.757
I'm the one who doesn't know
anything about love?

201
00:16:12.001 --> 00:16:16.769
[kisses. sighs. breathing heavily]

202
00:16:19.384 --> 00:16:22.775
Poor Kofun. [Sniffs. sighs]

203
00:16:24.264 --> 00:16:28.823
A year ago. you were an Alkenny.
A simple mountain boy.

204
00:16:29.310 --> 00:16:35.079
And now. you bear witness
to the rise and fall of kingdoms.

205
00:16:36.359 --> 00:16:39.292
There's so much you do not understand.

206
00:16:39.696 --> 00:16:43.004
I understand that you're a murderer
and a traitor.

207
00:16:48.580 --> 00:16:52.472
And what makes me any different
than your mother?

208
00:16:54.044 --> 00:16:55.391
Mmm.

209
00:16:57.172 --> 00:17:01.439
She rose up against the ordained queen.
Is she not a traitor?

210
00:17:02.177 --> 00:17:04.720
Last time I was in Pennsa.
she hosted an execution.

211
00:17:04.804 --> 00:17:06.653
Is she not a murderer?

212
00:17:08.224 --> 00:17:10.657
"Traitor." "murderer." they're just words.

213
00:17:11.770 --> 00:17:15.731
And their truth is dictated
by whichever side you happen to be on.

214
00:17:15.815 --> 00:17:18.359
- You're on the side of the Trivantians.
- No. [Chuckles]

215
00:17:18.443 --> 00:17:21.542
I am on the side of God.

216
00:17:22.405 --> 00:17:26.742
[sighs] How else do you explain
I'm still alive despite my death sentence.

217
00:17:26.826 --> 00:17:29.258
about to retake my throne?

218
00:17:30.246 --> 00:17:33.958
Your sightless child was sent to me by God

219
00:17:34.042 --> 00:17:37.336
to delay my execution
long enough to make my escape.

220
00:17:37.420 --> 00:17:40.478
He's your son too.
no matter how many times you deny it.

221
00:17:42.300 --> 00:17:47.944
He has served his holy purpose
and shall be remembered for it. Huh.

222
00:17:48.556 --> 00:17:50.071
You're a monster.

223
00:17:52.727 --> 00:17:54.020
[grunts]

224
00:17:54.104 --> 00:17:55.229
And you are a witch.

225
00:17:55.313 --> 00:17:57.106
[Kofun breathing heavily]

226
00:17:57.190 --> 00:17:59.900
Perhaps your mother's short reign
may have tricked you

227
00:17:59.984 --> 00:18:01.958
into thinking otherwise.

228
00:18:03.738 --> 00:18:07.283
But there are a hundred Witchfinders
right outside this tent

229
00:18:07.367 --> 00:18:12.175
who will happily burn you alive
just to remind you who you are.

230
00:18:12.997 --> 00:18:15.513
I'm just trying to remind you who you are.

231
00:18:16.792 --> 00:18:18.307
And who is that?

232
00:18:18.670 --> 00:18:21.102
[inhales deeply] You're Wolffe's mother.

233
00:18:24.134 --> 00:18:25.856
And he needs you.

234
00:18:28.013 --> 00:18:31.863
You said he was brought here to save you.
Well. maybe he's not done doing that.

235
00:18:34.060 --> 00:18:35.783
He's your son.

236
00:18:39.107 --> 00:18:40.747
He's your son. Sibeth.

237
00:18:48.324 --> 00:18:49.756
He's your son.

238
00:18:51.828 --> 00:18:54.538
- [Ranger grunting]
- [Tamacti Jun groaning]

239
00:18:54.622 --> 00:18:56.179
[screaming]

240
00:19:00.462 --> 00:19:01.462
[Haniwa] Please wake up.

241
00:19:01.546 --> 00:19:03.561
Mmm. Maghra.

242
00:19:08.470 --> 00:19:10.777
[Haniwa]
Oh. please wake up. please wake up.

243
00:19:11.014 --> 00:19:12.519
[Baba Voss] <i>What is your name?</i>

244
00:19:15.935 --> 00:19:17.533
You won't tell me your name?

245
00:19:19.230 --> 00:19:20.912
I don't want to lie to you.

246
00:19:24.402 --> 00:19:26.250
Are you the leader of the Alkenny?

247
00:19:27.238 --> 00:19:28.544
Yes.

248
00:19:30.283 --> 00:19:31.756
But you're not from here.

249
00:19:33.411 --> 00:19:35.997
I don't know your accent.
but it's not from the mountains.

250
00:19:36.081 --> 00:19:38.596
- Are you being pursued?
- No.

251
00:19:39.209 --> 00:19:40.890
You said you didn't wanna lie.

252
00:19:44.756 --> 00:19:47.633
I was being pursued.
but I've been traveling for a long time.

253
00:19:47.717 --> 00:19:49.232
and I left no trail.

254
00:19:49.928 --> 00:19:51.234
You can't know that.

255
00:19:52.013 --> 00:19:53.569
No. I can't.

256
00:19:55.934 --> 00:19:58.616
Rest up.
You will leave as soon as you can walk.

257
00:19:59.312 --> 00:20:01.577
That might take a bit longer
than you think.

258
00:20:02.607 --> 00:20:03.913
Why is that?

259
00:20:04.734 --> 00:20:06.165
I'm with child.

260
00:20:06.945 --> 00:20:09.127
[Wolffe crying]

261
00:20:09.948 --> 00:20:11.504
[Haniwa] She's waking up.

262
00:20:12.200 --> 00:20:14.298
Maghra. Maghra.

263
00:20:16.287 --> 00:20:17.593
Baba.

264
00:20:17.872 --> 00:20:21.334
[sighs] I am here with Haniwa.

265
00:20:21.418 --> 00:20:22.724
[Maghra] Ah.

266
00:20:23.837 --> 00:20:25.713
- [Baba Voss shushes]
- I'm so glad you're back.

267
00:20:25.797 --> 00:20:27.395
I was so worried.

268
00:20:28.425 --> 00:20:31.441
The house just... just flew apart.

269
00:20:32.095 --> 00:20:35.862
I know. It's the God Thunder. The bombs.

270
00:20:36.516 --> 00:20:38.323
You were not able to stop them?

271
00:20:39.019 --> 00:20:40.325
No.

272
00:20:41.271 --> 00:20:42.271
Wolffe!

273
00:20:42.355 --> 00:20:45.496
It's okay. It's okay.
He is safe. You saved him.

274
00:20:48.528 --> 00:20:51.419
Where's Kofun? Why is he not here?

275
00:20:52.282 --> 00:20:53.963
We sent him ahead to warn you.

276
00:20:54.242 --> 00:20:55.451
No. he's not been here.

277
00:20:55.535 --> 00:20:58.468
- [Haniwa] Where is he? He could be hurt.
- We will find him.

278
00:20:58.747 --> 00:21:01.387
- It's all my fault.
- [Haniwa gasps]

279
00:21:02.000 --> 00:21:03.000
[sniffles]

280
00:21:03.084 --> 00:21:05.962
Mama. Don't be ridiculous.

281
00:21:06.046 --> 00:21:09.187
[Baba Voss] No. you did your best
to make peace with Trivantes.

282
00:21:10.759 --> 00:21:14.525
No. it's not Trivantes.
[sniffles] It's Sibeth.

283
00:21:15.555 --> 00:21:16.931
How could that even be?

284
00:21:17.015 --> 00:21:18.933
Sibeth made an alliance

285
00:21:19.017 --> 00:21:22.158
between the rebel Witchfinders
and Tormada's army.

286
00:21:22.354 --> 00:21:24.952
I shielded her from execution.

287
00:21:25.774 --> 00:21:27.914
I let the Witchfinders live.

288
00:21:29.152 --> 00:21:32.126
I created the army
that will now destroy us.

289
00:21:34.949 --> 00:21:37.423
I need to go outside. [Grunts]

290
00:21:39.162 --> 00:21:42.845
Wait. wait. Mama. Mama.

291
00:21:43.291 --> 00:21:45.390
[Maghra] Haniwa. what do you see?

292
00:21:45.585 --> 00:21:50.687
[Haniwa] The huts are on fire.
There are dead and wounded everywhere.

293
00:21:52.676 --> 00:21:58.111
People are just wandering around…

294
00:22:00.308 --> 00:22:02.115
And they look terrified.

295
00:22:02.394 --> 00:22:07.370
Of course they're terrified.
Fire is falling from the sky like rain.

296
00:22:07.857 --> 00:22:10.067
There's no more fire falling from the sky.

297
00:22:10.151 --> 00:22:11.457
[Maghra] For now.

298
00:22:12.946 --> 00:22:15.378
Sibeth is letting us know
she's in control.

299
00:22:16.324 --> 00:22:20.202
Tamacti. assemble the Royal Guard
to put out the fires.

300
00:22:20.286 --> 00:22:22.121
and gather and treat the wounded.

301
00:22:22.205 --> 00:22:25.666
Evacuate those who can move quickly
to Al to on a

302
00:22:25.750 --> 00:22:29.434
where we will regroup
and be ready to fight.

303
00:22:32.924 --> 00:22:34.926
[Baba Voss] We must find your brother.

304
00:22:35.010 --> 00:22:39.055
We found Mama and Wolffe.
We'll find Kofun.

305
00:22:39.139 --> 00:22:40.820
[Baba Voss sighs]

306
00:22:41.224 --> 00:22:42.530
Come. Mama.

307
00:22:52.569 --> 00:22:58.338
Kofun! I'm sorry we haven't been
properly introduced until now.

308
00:23:00.076 --> 00:23:03.926
It's been a busy time.
as I'm sure you know.

309
00:23:05.498 --> 00:23:06.707
I know who you are.

310
00:23:06.791 --> 00:23:10.350
[chuckles] Yes. I'm sure you do.

311
00:23:11.713 --> 00:23:14.520
[groans] And I just wanna say.

312
00:23:15.216 --> 00:23:20.860
that as dire as things may feel now.
you do still have options.

313
00:23:22.015 --> 00:23:23.099
Options?

314
00:23:23.183 --> 00:23:29.494
Mmm. Your gifts have not always
been properly appreciated. Hmm?

315
00:23:31.358 --> 00:23:35.375
Well. the...
The Payans think you're a witch.

316
00:23:35.904 --> 00:23:39.921
Trivantians think you're a threat
to the republic. and... and me…

317
00:23:41.868 --> 00:23:43.424
I admire you.

318
00:23:44.537 --> 00:23:47.804
I understand your potential. Mmm?

319
00:23:48.166 --> 00:23:49.792
[chuckles] If you were to join me...

320
00:23:49.876 --> 00:23:51.419
You tried to kill us.

321
00:23:51.503 --> 00:23:55.561
Well. yes. but that was before.
Things have changed.

322
00:23:55.840 --> 00:24:00.094
Certainly. I had no idea
I'd be allied with Queen Kane.

323
00:24:00.178 --> 00:24:01.484
[chuckles]

324
00:24:02.055 --> 00:24:03.931
She'll kill you when she's done with you.

325
00:24:04.015 --> 00:24:05.488
Exactly.

326
00:24:05.767 --> 00:24:09.353
Or maybe I will kill her.
Or maybe nobody will kill anybody.

327
00:24:09.437 --> 00:24:10.743
[chuckles]

328
00:24:11.398 --> 00:24:15.943
Every day is a new day. Kofun.
Today could be a new day for you.

329
00:24:16.027 --> 00:24:17.111
Fuck you.

330
00:24:17.195 --> 00:24:19.210
[chuckles] Yes. of course.

331
00:24:20.365 --> 00:24:23.576
Boys your age
always seem to think they know so much.

332
00:24:23.660 --> 00:24:26.829
when really. they're just too stupid
to realize what they don't know.

333
00:24:26.913 --> 00:24:28.497
I know my father will kill you.

334
00:24:28.581 --> 00:24:32.877
Ah. like I said. Stupid.
We'll have plenty of time to educate you.

335
00:24:32.961 --> 00:24:34.267
What is it?

336
00:24:34.963 --> 00:24:37.186
[Witchfinder 1]
The queen has sent for him.

337
00:24:37.632 --> 00:24:38.938
[Tormada] What for?

338
00:24:40.719 --> 00:24:42.525
[Witchfinder 1] Ask her yourself.

339
00:24:44.014 --> 00:24:46.612
[Kofun grunts]

340
00:25:05.035 --> 00:25:06.341
[sighs]

341
00:25:19.382 --> 00:25:21.939
[Wren] Their camp's
about 100 heartbeats due east.

342
00:25:22.844 --> 00:25:24.317
How many soldiers?

343
00:25:26.890 --> 00:25:29.238
[Wren] I can see about 50 or so.

344
00:25:32.187 --> 00:25:33.743
Where are the rest?

345
00:25:34.689 --> 00:25:36.315
[door creaks]

346
00:25:36.399 --> 00:25:38.456
[sighs. breathing shakily]

347
00:25:40.111 --> 00:25:41.501
[whispering] Hush.

348
00:25:43.281 --> 00:25:45.283
[Tamacti Jun]
There's no way out of the city.

349
00:25:45.367 --> 00:25:46.867
[Maghra] Will they invade?

350
00:25:46.951 --> 00:25:48.257
I don't think so.

351
00:25:48.995 --> 00:25:53.096
If they can continue to launch bombs.
why risk soldiers?

352
00:25:53.458 --> 00:25:57.350
Sibeth wants her city back.
Why would she destroy it?

353
00:25:57.545 --> 00:25:59.894
[Tamacti Jun]
She could've launched many more.

354
00:26:00.423 --> 00:26:04.399
but the fact that we're still standing
means she wants the city whole.

355
00:26:05.053 --> 00:26:08.236
[clears throat] To do that.
she would have to send in her army.

356
00:26:10.892 --> 00:26:13.853
If Harlan and Trovere
were able to make their case in Trivantes.

357
00:26:13.937 --> 00:26:16.828
they could be on their way back now
with reinforcements.

358
00:26:17.107 --> 00:26:20.331
Mama. Harlan is dead.

359
00:26:26.241 --> 00:26:27.797
He died to save me.

360
00:26:35.583 --> 00:26:36.889
Mama. um...

361
00:26:37.752 --> 00:26:42.228
He. um. wanted me
to give something to you.

362
00:26:48.805 --> 00:26:50.111
A key?

363
00:26:51.808 --> 00:26:53.114
What's it for?

364
00:26:53.518 --> 00:26:56.659
[Haniwa]
I don't know. He said it might help.

365
00:26:58.106 --> 00:26:59.954
[breathing heavily]

366
00:27:11.995 --> 00:27:13.634
Haniwa?

367
00:27:14.122 --> 00:27:15.456
[Haniwa] Kofun.

368
00:27:15.540 --> 00:27:16.846
Kofun?

369
00:27:17.584 --> 00:27:19.460
- You okay?
- Are you okay?

370
00:27:19.544 --> 00:27:22.435
- Yeah. Ah. Papa.
- [Baba Voss grunts]

371
00:27:22.797 --> 00:27:24.215
Where have you been?

372
00:27:24.299 --> 00:27:27.565
Sibeth.
She captured me just outside the city.

373
00:27:30.764 --> 00:27:33.432
[kisses] She sent a message.

374
00:27:33.516 --> 00:27:34.934
A message?

375
00:27:35.018 --> 00:27:36.532
Yeah. she tied it.

376
00:27:40.315 --> 00:27:43.665
She wants your abdication
and total surrender.

377
00:27:45.737 --> 00:27:47.919
You'll walk alone to her camp.

378
00:27:48.281 --> 00:27:52.382
where you will forfeit your crown
and kingdom to her.

379
00:27:53.828 --> 00:27:55.454
She says if you don't go soon.

380
00:27:55.538 --> 00:28:00.473
then she'll turn Pennsa
and everyone in it into ash.

381
00:28:03.463 --> 00:28:05.019
[walking stick bangs]

382
00:28:10.261 --> 00:28:11.693
[Kofun sighs]

383
00:28:12.931 --> 00:28:17.824
She doesn't just want her kingdom back.
She wants to punish me.

384
00:28:18.645 --> 00:28:21.355
- You can't go.
- We're not having this argument. Haniwa.

385
00:28:21.439 --> 00:28:23.024
- Of course I'm going.
- She'll kill you.

386
00:28:23.108 --> 00:28:26.708
She'll kill all of us
and so many more if I don't go.

387
00:28:28.738 --> 00:28:32.755
She is my sister.
and as much as I despised her.

388
00:28:33.451 --> 00:28:35.953
when the moment came.
I found myself unable to kill her.

389
00:28:36.037 --> 00:28:38.623
Maybe she'll have the same hesitation
about killing me.

390
00:28:38.707 --> 00:28:40.207
[groans] You don't believe that.

391
00:28:40.291 --> 00:28:44.017
[sighs] Ju... It doesn't matter.
I-I have to go. I can't let her just…

392
00:28:44.838 --> 00:28:46.339
- [Baba Voss] Maghra!
- [Haniwa] Mama!

393
00:28:46.423 --> 00:28:51.524
[Baba Voss groans. exhales sharply.
shushes]

394
00:28:51.803 --> 00:28:53.735
[Baba Voss] <i>Paris says you will not eat.</i>

395
00:28:54.139 --> 00:28:58.197
Why am I not allowed to leave this cave?
Am I your prisoner?

396
00:28:59.436 --> 00:29:02.827
The villagers...
They are suspicious of strangers.

397
00:29:03.440 --> 00:29:05.608
It is not safe for you to be out there.

398
00:29:05.692 --> 00:29:08.249
Well. if they don't want me here.
then I'll leave.

399
00:29:08.570 --> 00:29:10.251
And where will you go?

400
00:29:13.408 --> 00:29:17.008
[sighs] You haven't even told me
your name or where you're from.

401
00:29:18.204 --> 00:29:21.596
If you want us to trust you.
you must trust us.

402
00:29:22.917 --> 00:29:24.349
You can trust me.

403
00:29:25.920 --> 00:29:27.560
Why would I trust you?

404
00:29:28.131 --> 00:29:30.396
Well.
I'm the one who's been protecting you.

405
00:29:33.386 --> 00:29:34.692
It's Maghra.

406
00:29:35.889 --> 00:29:39.197
- What?
- My name is Maghra.

407
00:29:40.060 --> 00:29:43.493
Maghra? What kinda name is Maghra?

408
00:29:44.189 --> 00:29:46.565
What kind of a name is Baba?

409
00:29:46.649 --> 00:29:49.707
[snickers] That's a fair point. Maghra.

410
00:29:54.074 --> 00:29:56.089
Why are you the one protecting me?

411
00:29:57.952 --> 00:30:00.760
Because I was once in the same position
that you are in.

412
00:30:01.539 --> 00:30:03.971
And how did you get the villagers
to trust you?

413
00:30:05.126 --> 00:30:07.016
I defeated their strongest warrior.

414
00:30:08.630 --> 00:30:10.687
So. I guess I have to defeat you.

415
00:30:12.550 --> 00:30:14.524
[chuckles] Yes.

416
00:30:23.978 --> 00:30:25.284
[Haniwa] Mama?

417
00:30:28.566 --> 00:30:29.872
Are you okay?

418
00:30:30.819 --> 00:30:32.375
[Baba Voss] Maghra.

419
00:30:34.197 --> 00:30:35.837
Yeah. I'm fine.

420
00:30:36.616 --> 00:30:38.131
We're all here.

421
00:30:39.202 --> 00:30:40.508
Hmm.

422
00:30:47.085 --> 00:30:49.086
I have... I have to go. [Grunts]

423
00:30:49.170 --> 00:30:52.048
No. no. no. We can't let you go.

424
00:30:52.132 --> 00:30:54.634
[Maghra breathing heavily]

425
00:30:54.718 --> 00:30:58.568
She will kill you where you stand.
and nothing will be gained.

426
00:31:00.140 --> 00:31:01.863
And what about Pennsa?

427
00:31:02.142 --> 00:31:04.644
She'll burn the entire city
just to spite me.

428
00:31:04.728 --> 00:31:05.937
I c-can't let that happen.

429
00:31:06.021 --> 00:31:09.398
If she's going to destroy Pennsa.
she will whether you are alive or dead.

430
00:31:09.482 --> 00:31:11.108
Is there no other way
to evacuate the city?

431
00:31:11.192 --> 00:31:14.195
- They have battalions at all the gates.
- So we fight our way out.

432
00:31:14.279 --> 00:31:17.128
The moment they hear resistance.
the bombs will come.

433
00:31:17.490 --> 00:31:19.464
The bombs will be coming either way.

434
00:31:19.826 --> 00:31:22.467
but this family will not be here
when they do.

435
00:31:23.580 --> 00:31:24.886
Harlan.

436
00:31:25.915 --> 00:31:27.347
[Baba Voss] What's that?

437
00:31:30.253 --> 00:31:32.935
[Maghra] He was always
three steps ahead of everyone.

438
00:31:33.882 --> 00:31:36.481
He was such an infuriating man.

439
00:31:37.761 --> 00:31:42.445
He gave me no reason to trust him.
Somehow. I did.

440
00:31:42.766 --> 00:31:47.033
Well. he could have saved himself.
but he came back for me.

441
00:31:52.901 --> 00:31:55.416
[chuckles] Maybe here?

442
00:31:56.696 --> 00:31:58.002
[sighs]

443
00:32:00.367 --> 00:32:02.451
[metal clanking]

444
00:32:02.535 --> 00:32:04.467
- No?
- No.

445
00:32:10.418 --> 00:32:12.016
He was in love with you.

446
00:32:25.475 --> 00:32:26.781
I used him.

447
00:32:29.229 --> 00:32:30.576
Now he's dead.

448
00:32:34.275 --> 00:32:38.584
Harlan didn't strike me as someone
who could be used if he didn't want to be.

449
00:32:46.329 --> 00:32:48.219
[sighing]

450
00:32:51.543 --> 00:32:52.932
What is it?

451
00:32:55.839 --> 00:32:57.770
- Mama.
- Can you bring it?

452
00:33:05.765 --> 00:33:07.016
[high-pitched clang]

453
00:33:07.100 --> 00:33:08.531
A sound wand?

454
00:33:09.769 --> 00:33:11.284
What else is in the box?

455
00:33:13.773 --> 00:33:15.163
Just this old map.

456
00:33:16.776 --> 00:33:18.082
[grunts]

457
00:33:24.409 --> 00:33:25.965
It looks like Pennsa.

458
00:33:26.578 --> 00:33:29.302
[Maghra] It is Pennsa. but…

459
00:33:31.124 --> 00:33:32.889
Something else. too.

460
00:33:34.377 --> 00:33:36.184
Oh. Harlan.

461
00:33:36.963 --> 00:33:39.645
Oh. you sneaky bastard.

462
00:33:39.966 --> 00:33:41.272
What is it?

463
00:33:41.885 --> 00:33:45.610
Tunnels. Smuggler's tunnels.

464
00:33:46.306 --> 00:33:47.987
Where do they go?

465
00:33:48.975 --> 00:33:51.824
Out of the city. Come on.

466
00:34:05.283 --> 00:34:07.048
[Tormada] My queen.

467
00:34:07.702 --> 00:34:10.093
Tormada. Come sit with me.

468
00:34:11.206 --> 00:34:12.512
[Tormada chuckles]

469
00:34:22.842 --> 00:34:27.026
How go your machinations? [Chuckles]

470
00:34:27.931 --> 00:34:31.322
By now.
our message will have been delivered.

471
00:34:33.353 --> 00:34:34.895
I have every confidence

472
00:34:34.979 --> 00:34:37.912
my sister will arrive shortly
to surrender.

473
00:34:38.775 --> 00:34:43.112
And when she does.
all of Paya will be ours.

474
00:34:43.196 --> 00:34:47.005
I think reducing Pennsa to rubble
sends a more dramatic message.

475
00:34:47.826 --> 00:34:52.176
I haven't endured all that I have
to rule over rubble and corpses.

476
00:34:53.331 --> 00:34:56.431
Paya will fall in line
with Maghra's surrender.

477
00:34:56.918 --> 00:34:59.392
It's not Paya I'm speaking of.

478
00:35:01.131 --> 00:35:02.437
Trivantes.

479
00:35:02.799 --> 00:35:04.897
Don't underestimate their might.

480
00:35:05.343 --> 00:35:07.150
Don't underestimate ours.

481
00:35:08.680 --> 00:35:10.361
Believe me. I don't.

482
00:35:11.474 --> 00:35:13.364
I do have one request.

483
00:35:13.685 --> 00:35:14.894
Hmm?

484
00:35:14.978 --> 00:35:17.618
- Your nephew.
- Kofun?

485
00:35:18.480 --> 00:35:21.372
I wish you had asked me
before you released him.

486
00:35:22.485 --> 00:35:24.570
Having lost
the rest of Jerlamarel's children.

487
00:35:24.654 --> 00:35:28.504
he would have been invaluable to me.

488
00:35:32.328 --> 00:35:35.414
You do realize that my arrangement
with the Witchfinders

489
00:35:35.498 --> 00:35:38.501
is based on an agreement
that all sighted are witches

490
00:35:38.585 --> 00:35:39.961
and must be burned?

491
00:35:40.045 --> 00:35:41.893
I won't need them forever.

492
00:35:42.755 --> 00:35:49.817
I have been working on adapting the system
to no longer require their sight. Hmm?

493
00:35:51.221 --> 00:35:52.640
Until then. though.

494
00:35:52.724 --> 00:35:56.866
the Witchfinders will just need to agree
to certain exceptions.

495
00:35:57.978 --> 00:36:00.536
- The Witchfinders can be dangerous.
- So can I.

496
00:36:01.983 --> 00:36:04.582
They have God on their side.

497
00:36:05.195 --> 00:36:10.254
I hope you don't take offense.
but I don't believe in God.

498
00:36:11.034 --> 00:36:12.535
- You don't?
- Mmm.

499
00:36:12.619 --> 00:36:13.925
Oh.

500
00:36:17.290 --> 00:36:18.721
[groans]

501
00:36:19.834 --> 00:36:21.140
[grunts]

502
00:36:21.586 --> 00:36:24.477
Maybe you haven't met the right one yet.

503
00:36:24.839 --> 00:36:26.299
[grunts]

504
00:36:26.383 --> 00:36:28.467
[moans. breathing heavily]

505
00:36:28.551 --> 00:36:29.719
[groans]

506
00:36:29.803 --> 00:36:31.109
[groans]

507
00:36:34.516 --> 00:36:37.351
- [Wren] Are you interpreting that right?
- [Haniwa] Yes.

508
00:36:37.435 --> 00:36:39.492
All the landmarks are accounted for.

509
00:36:39.771 --> 00:36:41.077
[Wren] Let me see it.

510
00:36:48.530 --> 00:36:49.836
This way.

511
00:37:46.379 --> 00:37:49.020
Well. according to the map.
it should be right here.

512
00:37:55.221 --> 00:37:56.527
I don't see anything.

513
00:37:57.891 --> 00:37:59.489
Well. maybe the map's wrong.

514
00:38:00.560 --> 00:38:02.283
You didn't know Harlan.

515
00:38:03.980 --> 00:38:05.828
The map isn't wrong.

516
00:38:06.941 --> 00:38:08.247
[knocks]

517
00:38:11.404 --> 00:38:13.086
Hello?

518
00:38:19.704 --> 00:38:21.135
There's nothing here.

519
00:38:39.099 --> 00:38:40.405
[metal clangs]

520
00:38:48.692 --> 00:38:49.998
[groans]

521
00:38:55.240 --> 00:38:56.546
[gasps]

522
00:38:58.410 --> 00:38:59.716
I'll be right back.

523
00:39:00.995 --> 00:39:03.886
[breathes heavily]

524
00:39:37.532 --> 00:39:39.422
We followed the tunnel to its end.

525
00:39:39.951 --> 00:39:42.411
It comes out in a small cave
in the mountains.

526
00:39:42.495 --> 00:39:44.010
Just west of Pennsa.

527
00:39:44.330 --> 00:39:47.875
If we move now. we can be halfway
to Al to on a before they know we're gone.

528
00:39:47.959 --> 00:39:50.294
And what stops them
from bringing bombs to Al to on a?

529
00:39:50.378 --> 00:39:52.463
Sibeth's army is still small.

530
00:39:52.547 --> 00:39:55.800
We can regroup in Al to on a.
Gather soldiers.

531
00:39:55.884 --> 00:39:59.011
Be ready before they...
They can establish position

532
00:39:59.095 --> 00:40:00.401
as they did here.

533
00:40:01.514 --> 00:40:03.154
We've no time to lose.

534
00:40:03.975 --> 00:40:08.910
Captain Gosset. have your men begin
rounding up the citizens immediately.

535
00:40:09.647 --> 00:40:11.746
No one takes more than they can carry.

536
00:40:11.941 --> 00:40:16.209
Haniwa. you and Wren direct the captain
to the entrance you found.

537
00:40:21.910 --> 00:40:25.802
Kofun. Tamacti. Ranger.

538
00:40:27.040 --> 00:40:28.721
Leave us for a moment.

539
00:40:35.757 --> 00:40:37.730
[Baba Voss groans]

540
00:40:41.179 --> 00:40:42.485
Baba.

541
00:40:45.642 --> 00:40:47.240
You haven't said a word.

542
00:40:48.103 --> 00:40:53.579
[sighs sharply] You are queen.
You know what's best for your people.

543
00:40:54.693 --> 00:40:55.818
[groans]

544
00:40:55.902 --> 00:40:58.195
Yes. I must take care of the kingdom.

545
00:40:58.279 --> 00:41:03.131
But you are my husband.
And the father to Haniwa and Kofun.

546
00:41:04.494 --> 00:41:07.135
So you must decide what is best for us.

547
00:41:10.417 --> 00:41:11.848
I don't understand.

548
00:41:13.169 --> 00:41:16.060
My sister hunted us for 17 years.

549
00:41:17.382 --> 00:41:20.773
She didn't stop then.
and she won't stop now.

550
00:41:21.886 --> 00:41:24.027
She will never stop hunting this family.

551
00:41:29.060 --> 00:41:30.742
So what are you saying?

552
00:41:32.313 --> 00:41:37.123
I'm saying that you were right all along.

553
00:41:39.112 --> 00:41:41.489
Once we lead the people out of Pennsa.

554
00:41:41.573 --> 00:41:46.883
you and I. and Kofun. and Wolffe
and Haniwa. we shall go far away.

555
00:41:47.245 --> 00:41:50.011
Back up into the mountains.
or further even.

556
00:41:50.248 --> 00:41:52.930
where we can be the family we once were.

557
00:41:55.336 --> 00:41:56.337
Maybe with me gone.

558
00:41:56.421 --> 00:42:00.355
my sister will be less inclined
to direct her wrath at the Payans.

559
00:42:04.262 --> 00:42:05.568
Are you sure?

560
00:42:08.558 --> 00:42:12.158
I have been a mother much longer
than I've been a queen.

561
00:42:13.271 --> 00:42:17.538
And if my family coming first
means I'm a bad queen…

562
00:42:19.694 --> 00:42:24.128
Well. then it just proves
that I... I shouldn't be one.

563
00:42:26.910 --> 00:42:28.549
I don't feel anything.

564
00:42:29.162 --> 00:42:31.247
- Here.
- You mean here?

565
00:42:31.331 --> 00:42:33.721
- [laughs]
- Oh. there it is.

566
00:42:36.002 --> 00:42:38.045
- Here. Do you feel that?
- Where? Oh. here.

567
00:42:38.129 --> 00:42:41.104
- No. Still nothing.
- [laughs]

568
00:42:42.509 --> 00:42:46.053
I think you just like having an excuse
to put your hands on me.

569
00:42:46.137 --> 00:42:50.238
- I think maybe you like my hands on you.
- Well. mmm. maybe I do.

570
00:42:55.980 --> 00:42:57.537
You still feel nothing?

571
00:42:59.567 --> 00:43:01.040
Maybe it's scared of me.

572
00:43:02.320 --> 00:43:05.670
Mmm. Maybe it's not the baby who's scared.

573
00:43:06.825 --> 00:43:10.717
What are you talking about?
Why would I be scared? [Kisses]

574
00:43:11.329 --> 00:43:13.344
Because you've never had a child.

575
00:43:16.543 --> 00:43:19.392
And this child. would it be mine?

576
00:43:26.011 --> 00:43:27.817
Do you want it to be yours?

577
00:43:31.433 --> 00:43:33.114
As much as I want you.

578
00:43:35.812 --> 00:43:38.411
Then we are both yours.

579
00:43:44.279 --> 00:43:47.378
- [Maghra sighs]
- [Baba Voss] I love you. [Kissing]

580
00:43:48.491 --> 00:43:49.964
[groans]

581
00:43:51.161 --> 00:43:54.677
I love you. Baba Voss.

582
00:43:56.791 --> 00:43:58.598
I love you. Maghra Voss.

583
00:43:58.960 --> 00:44:01.517
[both chuckling]

584
00:44:02.380 --> 00:44:04.562
You think it will always be like this?

585
00:44:05.842 --> 00:44:07.357
You fear it will not?

586
00:44:08.303 --> 00:44:09.859
I fear for my child.

587
00:44:12.015 --> 00:44:13.488
[Baba Voss sighs]

588
00:44:15.310 --> 00:44:17.019
I swear to you that I will die

589
00:44:17.103 --> 00:44:19.827
before I allow anything to happen
to you or our child.

590
00:44:21.775 --> 00:44:23.539
And we will protect you.

591
00:44:24.152 --> 00:44:25.458
Yes.

592
00:44:26.321 --> 00:44:28.739
- Yes. you protect me. I need that.
- Yes.

593
00:44:28.823 --> 00:44:30.366
- [gasping] Oh. wait.
- What?

594
00:44:30.450 --> 00:44:31.909
- [gasps]
- [Maghra] You feel that?

595
00:44:31.993 --> 00:44:33.536
- [Baba Voss] There it is.
- Yeah?

596
00:44:33.620 --> 00:44:36.302
- It's kicking. And again.
- [laughing] Yeah.

597
00:44:36.998 --> 00:44:40.001
- Oh. it's a very angry baby.
- Oh. wow. [Giggles]

598
00:44:40.085 --> 00:44:42.058
And he has a temper like his mother.

599
00:44:42.462 --> 00:44:45.381
A temper? I don't have a temper.
What are you talking about?

600
00:44:45.465 --> 00:44:48.815
- No. of course you don't.
- I don't have a temper. What do you mean?

601
00:44:49.386 --> 00:44:50.803
That's rich coming from you.

602
00:44:50.887 --> 00:44:54.015
- [Baba Voss] Look at that. Sassy baby.
- Uh-huh. Sassy ba...

603
00:44:54.099 --> 00:44:56.309
[Baba Voss]
Sassy. angry baby like your mother.

604
00:44:56.393 --> 00:44:57.991
[both chuckling]

605
00:45:02.232 --> 00:45:06.124
- [Baba Voss whistles]
- [No barking]

606
00:45:13.410 --> 00:45:15.466
[Ranger] Your dog stinks.

607
00:45:15.745 --> 00:45:17.510
- [exhales deeply]
- [Baba Voss] Up.

608
00:45:18.707 --> 00:45:20.082
No. that's me. [Chuckles]

609
00:45:20.166 --> 00:45:21.597
Up. boy.

610
00:45:22.794 --> 00:45:24.642
You should go home. my friend.

611
00:45:24.921 --> 00:45:29.272
[Ranger sighs]
My home was blown up. thanks to you.

612
00:45:29.843 --> 00:45:33.026
- [Baba Voss] You know what I mean.
- Ah. you know what I mean.

613
00:45:35.265 --> 00:45:36.738
[sighs]

614
00:45:37.892 --> 00:45:41.743
I've avoided humanity for almost 20 years.

615
00:45:43.106 --> 00:45:45.399
[inhales sharply]
And if I live through this.

616
00:45:45.483 --> 00:45:48.527
the day will soon come
where I will avoid them for another 20.

617
00:45:48.611 --> 00:45:51.627
[exhales deeply]
But today is not that day.

618
00:45:52.824 --> 00:45:54.130
Damn it. Ranger.

619
00:45:54.743 --> 00:45:56.118
If anything happens to you.

620
00:45:56.202 --> 00:45:58.885
Lu will hunt me down
and kill me in my sleep.

621
00:45:59.414 --> 00:46:04.001
No. She will wake you first.
so that you feel it when it happens.

622
00:46:04.085 --> 00:46:05.933
[both chuckling]

623
00:46:07.422 --> 00:46:10.355
I made the choice to leave the mountain.

624
00:46:10.842 --> 00:46:13.775
That may turn out
to have been a terrible mistake.

625
00:46:14.262 --> 00:46:17.848
but. as of this moment. my blade is sharp.

626
00:46:17.932 --> 00:46:21.102
My weed is good.
and the sun feels warm on my face.

627
00:46:21.186 --> 00:46:24.535
So. things being what they are.

628
00:46:25.482 --> 00:46:28.706
I think I will stay
and find out how the story ends.

629
00:46:30.236 --> 00:46:32.418
[inhales deeply] What do you think?

630
00:46:34.032 --> 00:46:37.493
- I think you smoke too much of that herb.
- [laughs]

631
00:46:37.577 --> 00:46:39.662
- Yeah. maybe.
- Too much.

632
00:46:39.746 --> 00:46:42.136
[groaning]

633
00:46:42.415 --> 00:46:44.597
[Ranger] Or maybe you don't smoke enough.

634
00:46:45.752 --> 00:46:48.226
[both groaning]

635
00:47:19.786 --> 00:47:22.093
[chattering]

636
00:47:24.708 --> 00:47:26.792
[Tamacti Jun]
We have rounded up every citizen.

637
00:47:26.876 --> 00:47:29.100
Those not yet here are on their way.

638
00:47:29.546 --> 00:47:31.144
I hear unrest in your voice.

639
00:47:34.300 --> 00:47:39.152
Have you ever wondered
why we eat bison and deer. but not bear?

640
00:47:41.099 --> 00:47:43.559
When you hunt bison and deer.
they run away.

641
00:47:43.643 --> 00:47:45.783
and that makes them vulnerable.

642
00:47:46.229 --> 00:47:49.912
If you hunt a bear.
the bear hunts you back.

643
00:47:50.817 --> 00:47:54.250
As a general rule. those who flee
are the ones that get eaten.

644
00:47:54.612 --> 00:47:57.239
[Maghra] You agreed.
we stand a better chance in Al to on a?

645
00:47:57.323 --> 00:48:01.549
[Tamacti Jun] Yes.
but first we have to make it to Al to on a.

646
00:48:03.788 --> 00:48:05.331
Mom. I'm so sorry.

647
00:48:05.415 --> 00:48:07.333
- I'm so... This is my fault.
- Kofun. Kofun.

648
00:48:07.417 --> 00:48:10.628
- It's my fault. I let her go.
- I let her live.

649
00:48:10.712 --> 00:48:13.965
Hey. hey. my loves. Listen to me.

650
00:48:14.049 --> 00:48:15.688
[fingers snapping] Haniwa.

651
00:48:16.885 --> 00:48:21.235
You are not just my family.
You are the best that I have ever known.

652
00:48:22.891 --> 00:48:26.115
I have been carrying blame on my shoulders

653
00:48:27.020 --> 00:48:32.121
for the Alkenny. for Edo.
for everything that came before.

654
00:48:34.069 --> 00:48:37.280
And I have been learning
from my occasionally wise friend. Ranger.

655
00:48:37.364 --> 00:48:41.005
that blaming yourself
does no one any good.

656
00:48:42.160 --> 00:48:45.093
You must pay attention to what lies ahead.
not behind.

657
00:48:46.331 --> 00:48:48.262
- Yes.
- Is that what you would do?

658
00:48:50.460 --> 00:48:53.087
- It's what a wiser man would do.
- [Maghra snickers]

659
00:48:53.171 --> 00:48:55.478
[all chuckle]

660
00:48:56.591 --> 00:48:58.022
[Baba Voss groans]

661
00:49:00.970 --> 00:49:03.820
Come. my loves. Let's get out of here.

662
00:49:08.728 --> 00:49:09.979
- Mama.
- [Maghra] Mm-hmm.

663
00:49:10.063 --> 00:49:11.369
This way.

664
00:49:45.682 --> 00:49:47.947
[murmuring]

665
00:50:06.911 --> 00:50:09.510
[Bella's mom] Come on. baby. No. no.

666
00:50:10.415 --> 00:50:12.792
- We have to keep moving.
- [Bella] I want to go home.

667
00:50:12.876 --> 00:50:15.544
[Bella's Mom]
We can't go home. We have to keep moving.

668
00:50:15.628 --> 00:50:18.895
- [Bella] No. I don't want to.
- [Bella's Mom] Bella. please.

669
00:50:19.466 --> 00:50:24.053
[Maghra] Excuse me. Is your name Bella?

670
00:50:24.137 --> 00:50:26.778
- Yes.
- Oh. that's a beautiful name.

671
00:50:27.974 --> 00:50:29.141
My name is Maghra.

672
00:50:29.225 --> 00:50:32.103
[gasps] My queen. [Breathing heavily]

673
00:50:32.187 --> 00:50:34.939
- Are you scared. Bella?
- Yes.

674
00:50:35.023 --> 00:50:36.871
I'm scared too.

675
00:50:37.817 --> 00:50:40.792
But you know.
I have something that helps me.

676
00:50:44.532 --> 00:50:45.838
Feel.

677
00:50:47.035 --> 00:50:49.300
It is a sound wand.

678
00:50:49.579 --> 00:50:52.081
And. you know.
it's not just any sound wand.

679
00:50:52.165 --> 00:50:55.098
It is the queen's sound wand.

680
00:50:56.211 --> 00:50:57.517
Now listen.

681
00:50:57.837 --> 00:51:02.216
[metal clangs. high-pitched ringing]

682
00:51:02.300 --> 00:51:07.430
You know. I've been trying to find someone
who can hold it for me and keep it safe.

683
00:51:07.514 --> 00:51:09.724
- You think you could do that?
- Yes.

684
00:51:09.808 --> 00:51:11.406
[sighs] Good.

685
00:51:13.144 --> 00:51:16.536
You bring it through the tunnel for me.

686
00:51:16.815 --> 00:51:20.623
And if you get scared.
you just hit it against the wall.

687
00:51:21.528 --> 00:51:23.418
and you listen to the sound.

688
00:51:23.863 --> 00:51:27.422
And you remember
that you are an emissary of the queen.

689
00:51:28.034 --> 00:51:29.340
All right?

690
00:51:30.036 --> 00:51:32.927
[kisses] Now. go on. brave girl.

691
00:51:38.294 --> 00:51:39.892
- Maghra.
- Yes.

692
00:51:40.213 --> 00:51:41.519
[Baba Voss] My love.

693
00:51:44.843 --> 00:51:47.150
You are a true queen. my love.

694
00:51:50.140 --> 00:51:54.115
To your people. And to me.

695
00:51:55.311 --> 00:51:58.328
[kissing]

696
00:52:00.066 --> 00:52:01.372
Come on.

697
00:52:15.874 --> 00:52:18.598
[metal clangs. high-pitched ringing]

698
00:52:24.174 --> 00:52:28.024
At this rate.
we'll be underground for another day.

699
00:52:28.553 --> 00:52:31.194
We go as slow as our slowest citizen.

700
00:52:32.057 --> 00:52:35.031
Baba Voss. why don't you take up the rear?

701
00:52:36.936 --> 00:52:38.242
Baba!

702
00:52:39.230 --> 00:52:40.536
Baba?

703
00:52:41.441 --> 00:52:44.248
- Where is he?
- He was just here a moment ago.

704
00:52:45.862 --> 00:52:47.168
Stop!

705
00:52:48.615 --> 00:52:49.921
Haniwa!

706
00:52:53.578 --> 00:52:54.884
[Maghra] Baba?

707
00:52:55.580 --> 00:52:57.512
- Where is he?
- Baba?

708
00:52:58.208 --> 00:52:59.514
I don't know.

709
00:53:00.752 --> 00:53:01.752
Dad!

710
00:53:01.836 --> 00:53:04.672
Perhaps he's gone back
to help the stragglers.

711
00:53:04.756 --> 00:53:07.021
- I'll send some scouts to find him.
- No.

712
00:53:07.967 --> 00:53:09.524
He won't be there.

713
00:53:09.803 --> 00:53:11.721
What do you mean? What did he tell you?

714
00:53:11.805 --> 00:53:14.779
He told me nothing
because he knows I would've stopped him.

715
00:53:15.266 --> 00:53:18.366
I know your father
better than I know myself. and so do you.

716
00:53:18.687 --> 00:53:20.104
He's gone back.

717
00:53:20.188 --> 00:53:22.898
- What?
- Why would he do that?

718
00:53:22.982 --> 00:53:25.623
He can't defeat an entire army by himself.

719
00:53:28.029 --> 00:53:29.794
He's gone to kill my sister.

720
00:53:54.431 --> 00:53:57.530
- [kisses]
- [whining]

721
00:54:06.526 --> 00:54:08.750
[Ranger inhales deeply]

722
00:54:10.697 --> 00:54:12.628
[sniffs]

723
00:54:16.411 --> 00:54:18.343
You really do smoke too much.

724
00:54:19.748 --> 00:54:21.054
No such thing.

725
00:54:26.963 --> 00:54:28.269
Where are you headed?

726
00:54:30.258 --> 00:54:32.927
I'm gonna hunt down that demon queen
and cut out her heart.

727
00:54:33.011 --> 00:54:35.263
Aw. sounds like a terrible idea.

728
00:54:35.347 --> 00:54:36.555
Can I come?

729
00:54:36.639 --> 00:54:37.945
Sure.

730
00:54:38.850 --> 00:54:40.782
Beware of wolves. Baba Voss.

731
00:54:41.693 --> 00:54:43.249
We are the fucking wolves.

732
00:54:43.505 --> 00:54:44.811
All right.

733
00:54:45.305 --> 00:55:45.771
